request.description:
Returns JSON flow instead of a browser redirect.

scope must NOT include openid — it conflicts with resource= audience.
resource={{ENDUSER_AUDIENCE}} = https://ai-agent.pingdemo.com ensures the Subject Token
gets aud=["https://ai-agent.pingdemo.com"] and may_act is present.

Expected response:
```json
{
  "id": "<flow-id>",
  "status": "USERNAME_PASSWORD_REQUIRED",
  "_links": {
    "usernamePassword.check": { "href": "https://auth.pingone.com/{envId}/flows/{flowId}" }
  }
}
```

Exchange #2 (RFC 8693): Agent Exchanged Token + MCP Actor Token → MCP Exchanged Token (Token 3).

PingOne validates: subject_token.act.sub == actor_token.aud[0] == mcp_client_id.
If valid, issues MCP Exchanged Token with nested act:
  aud = ["https://resource-server.pingdemo.com"]
  sub = <user-id> (preserved throughout)
  act = {
    "sub": "<MCP_CLIENT_ID>",      ← MCP performed Exchange #2
    "act": {
      "sub": "<AI_AGENT_CLIENT_ID>" ← AI Agent performed Exchange #1
    }
  }

PAZ enforces act.sub and act.act.sub as policy attributes.
Requires Token Exchange grant on BX Finance MCP Service App.
